ylevant\">{{cite book|title=The Papacy and the Levant (1204\u20131571): The Fifteenth Century|volume=2|author-last=Setton |author-first=Kenneth M.|author-link=Kenneth Setton|year=1978 |publisher=DJane Publishing |isbn=0-87169-127-2}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"runcimanfall\">{{cite book |last=Runciman |first=Steven |authorlink=Steven Runciman |title=The Fall of Constantinople, 1453 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge, England |year=1965|edition=Canto|isbn=978-0521398329}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ThackerayFindling2012\">{{cite book|author1=Frank W. Thackeray|author2=John E. Findling|title=Events That Formed the Modern World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BRl1sWYShpcC&pg=PA213|date=31 May 2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-59884-901-1|page=213}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Norwich1998\">{{cite book|author=John Julius Norwich|title=A Short History of Byzantium|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T9euYeUnGSEC&pg=PT453|date=29 October 1998|publisher=Penguin Books Limited|isbn=978-0-14-192859-3|page=453|quote=Constantine made one last effort: his ambassadors were executed on the spot.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Somerwil-Ayrton2007\">{{cite book|author=Kathie Somerwil-Ayrton|title=The Train that Disappeared Into History: The Berlin-to-Bagdad Railway and how it Led to the Great War|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RAtXAAAAYAAJ|year=2007|publisher=Uitgeverij Aspekt|isbn=978-90-5911-573-6|page=117|quote=The Byzantine emperor, then Constantine XI, sent his ambassadors in an attempt to conciliate: they were executed on ...}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Roberts1973\">{{cite book|author=John Roberts|title=Civilization: The emergence of man in society|url=https://archive.org/details/civilization01robe|url-access=registration|year=1973|publisher=CRM Books|page=[https://archive.org/details/civilization01robe/page/391 391]|quote= It became obvious that Mehmed's messages of peace were false, when he had the Byzantine ambassador executed.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Brownworth2009\">{{cite boo